31 the period for early voting or on election day, an elector is required, with certain exceptions,
32 to provide a current and valid driver’s license or identification card issued by this State,
33 another state, the District of Columbia or a territory of the United States or provide a tribal
34 identification card as proof of the elector’s identity. If the elector’s driver’s license or
35 identification card was issued by the Department of Motor Vehicles and shows the elector’s
36 current residential address, the driver’s license or identification card is also proof of the
37 elector’s residency. If the elector’s tribal identification card shows the elector’s current
38 residential address, the tribal identification card is also proof of the elector’s residency.
39 Sections [1] 1.7 and 2 provide that if the elector’s driver’s license or identification card
40 was not issued by the Department of Motor Vehicles, the elector may cast a provisional ballot
41 if he or she completes a written affirmation. Any such elector who casts a provisional ballot
42 must provide a current or valid driver’s license or identification card issued by the
43 Department, an interim document issued by the Department or a tribal identification card
44 demonstrating proof of residency by 5 p.m. on the Friday immediately following election day.
45 Sections [1] 1.7 and 2 also provide that if an elector’s driver’s license or identification
46 card issued by the Department of Motor Vehicles does not have the elector’s current
47 residential address, the elector may present an original, electronic or certified copy of a
48 document as proof of residency and that, for certain documents, such document must be dated
49 not more than 60 days before the date the elector is registering to vote.
50 Sections [1] 1.7 and 2 further provide that if an elector does not have a driver’s license or
51 identification card issued by this State, another state, the District of Columbia or any territory
52 of the United States or a tribal identification card, the elector may cast a provisional ballot if
53 he or she completes a written affirmation. Any such elector who casts a provisional ballot
54 must provide a current and valid driver’s license, identification card or interim document
55 issued by the Department of Motor Vehicles or a tribal identification card demonstrating proof
56 of identity and residency in this State by 5 p.m. on the Friday immediately following election
57 day.
58 Existing law authorizes the Director of the Department of Motor Vehicles to arrange for
59 extended hours of operation for offices of the Department in a county whose population is
60 100,000 or more (currently Clark and Washoe Counties). (NRS 481.057) Section 3 of this bill
61 provides that, in a county whose population is 100,000 or more, the Director is required to
62 arrange for the offices of the Department to remain open on Saturdays and Sundays and at
63 hours other than 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. for a person to only apply for the issuance or renewal of any
64 type of driver’s license or identification card issued by the Department: (1) during the 2 weeks
65 immediately preceding the last day to register to vote by mail for a primary election,
66 presidential preference primary election or general election; and (2) during the 6 calendar days
67 immediately following the day of a primary election, presidential preference primary election
68 or general election. Section 3 further prohibits the Department from requiring, in a county
69 whose population is 100,000 or more, a person to have an appointment to apply for the
70 issuance or renewal of any type of driver’s license or identification card issued by the
71 Department: (1) during the 2 weeks immediately preceding the last day to register to vote by
72 mail for a primary election, presidential preference primary election or general election; and
73 (2) during the 6 calendar days immediately following the day of a primary election,
74 presidential preference primary election or general election.

